snippet.textDisplay:
The exhaust ends in the middle because physics.
The longer it is, the more the torque curve translates towards the bottom end. In order to make peak power better, exhaust length cannot be too long on a performance-oriented engine. It is not, as you say, for an exhaust note or because they worry it "might get hung up on something", it's a V8 Biturbo and the Powertrain department definitely said no way that pipe is going any longer than exactly this.
snippet.textOriginal:
The exhaust ends in the middle because physics.
The longer it is, the more the torque curve translates towards the bottom end. In order to make peak power better, exhaust length cannot be too long on a performance-oriented engine. It is not, as you say, for an exhaust note or because they worry it "might get hung up on something", it's a V8 Biturbo and the Powertrain department definitely said no way that pipe is going any longer than exactly this.
